!!! Strict
%html{html_attrs}
  %head
    %title= "#{@interview.person + " on " if @interview && @interview.person}The Setup"
    %link{:href => '/stylesheets/screen.css', :media => 'screen', :rel => 'stylesheet', :type => 'text/css'}
    - if has_auth?
      %link{:href => '/stylesheets/admin.css', :media => 'screen', :rel => 'stylesheet', :type => 'text/css'}
    %link{:href => '/stylesheets/mobile.css', :media => 'only screen and (max-device-width: 480px)', :rel => 'stylesheet', :type => 'text/css'}
    %link{:href => '/feed', :type => 'application/atom+xml', :rel => 'alternate', :title => 'Atom feed'}
    %meta{:charset => 'utf8'}
    %meta{:name => 'viewport', :content => 'initial-scale = 0.59'}
  %body
    %header
      %h1
        %a{:href => "http://usesthis.com/", :title => "This is The Setup, a bunch of nerdy interviews."} the setup
        is a bunch of nerdy interviews
      %p#tagline What do people use to get the job done?
      - if has_auth?
        %p#admin
          = "Logged in"
          %a{:href => '/logout', :title => 'Give it up.'} (Logout)
    %section{:id => 'contents'}
      = yield
    %footer
      :markdown
        This is some sort of [waferbaby](http://waferbaby.com/ "Some website.") shindig. Sorry about that. Really.
        
        You can follow us [on Twitter](http://twitter.com/usesthis/ "Our Twitter account.") or subscribe to [the feed](/feed/ "The Atom feed for the site.").
        You can even grab [the source code](http://github.com/waferbaby/usesthis/ "The source code for this site."), if you're into that sort of thing.
        
        Unless otherwise noted, everything here is available via the [Attribution-Share Alike](http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.5/au/ "A Creative Commons license.") license. Sharing is fucking *cool*.